        <def>BUDDH: skr. jambu-dvīpa; pali jambu-dīpa; 閻浮 transliterates jambu which originally refers to a kind of tree (Eugenia jambolana) and 提 refers to dvīpa, 'continent'; in Buddhist cosmology this refers to the southern continent among the four continents surrounding Mt. Sumeru. Only this continent was thought of being in possession of a 'Diamond-seat' (jīngāng zuò 金剛座) which is the place where all Bodhisattvas gain enlightenment.</def>
